verbose_text: In the present study, with a different inflammatory stimulus, native GLP-2 treatment resulted in increased levels of the proinflammatory cytokines IL-1beta and IFNgamma and decreased amounts of the anti-inflammatory cytokines IL-10 and prohealing factor TGF-beta and yet healing appeared to proceed normally.
evidence: amounts of the anti-inflammatory cytokines IL-10 and prohealing factor TGF-beta
